---
const bullets = [
  "Automated limit price adjustment (“Anchor” engine)",
  "Top recommendations feed ranked for long-term accumulation",
  "One-tap limit order setup for linked brokerages (concept)",
  "Audit trail concept for every adjustment",
];
---

<section class="pt-14 pb-10">
  <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-12 md:items-center">
    <div class="md:col-span-7">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight leading-[1.05]" transition:name="headline">
        Stop watching charts. <span class="text-sky-400">Anchor</span> your entries and exits.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-neutral-300">
        TradeAnchor AI is a smart layer for U.S. retail investors that helps you buy low and sell high using automated,
        adaptive limit orders—built for long-term wealth building.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
        <a href="/waitlist" class="rounded-2xl bg-sky-500 px-5 py-3 font-medium text-neutral-950 hover:bg-sky-400 transition">
          Get early access
        </a>
        <a href="/product" class="rounded-2xl bg-white/5 px-5 py-3 font-medium text-white hover:bg-white/10 transition">
          See how it works
        </a>
      </div>

      <ul class="mt-8 grid gap-2 text-neutral-300">
        {bullets.map((b) => (
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-1 inline-block h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-sky-400"></span>
            <span>{b}</span>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="md:col-span-5">
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5 shadow-[0_0_0_1px_rgba(255,255,255,0.06)]">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-300">Today’s “Buy List” (mock)</p>
          <span class="text-xs text-neutral-400">Updated daily</span>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          {[
            { t: "MSFT", s: "High quality accumulation", p: "$402 → $392 limit" },
            { t: "AAPL", s: "Mean-reversion entry", p: "$196 → $189 limit" },
            { t: "NVDA", s: "Volatility-aware anchoring", p: "$620 → $588 limit" },
          ].map((row) => (
            <div class="rounded-2xl bg-neutral-950/40 p-4 ring-1 ring-white/10">
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
                <p class="font-medium">{row.t}</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-sky-300">{row.p}</p>
              </div>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-neutral-400">{row.s}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <div class="mt-5 rounded-2xl bg-sky-500/10 p-4 ring-1 ring-sky-400/20">
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-200">
            “Anchor” engine simulates adjusting your pending limit orders as support levels shift.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
